        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;font-family">Veg Samosa</h2>

        <img style="padding-left:250px;" src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQQmRSSvFxJNgZpSLWROtd2Qc0ZGd1lJa_Hpg&usqp=CAU" alt="Onion Samosa">
        <div id="en">
            <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;color:cyan;">
                    For the Outer layer:
                </li>
                <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                    <li>2 cups of all-purpose flour-175 grams</li>
                    <li>1 and 1/2 Spoons of Heated oil</li>
                    <li>Salt (Adjust to taste) </li>
                    <li>Water</li>
                </ul>

                <li style="text-decoration: underline;color:cyan;">For the Stuffing:</li>
                <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                    <li>2 large finely chopped onions(vertically)</li>
                    <li>3-4 green chilies, finely chopped (adjust to taste)</li>
                    <li>1/2 teaspoon ginger garlic paste</li>
                    <li>1/2 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to taste)</li>
                    <li>1/2 coriander powder</li>
                    <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
                    <li>A pinch of Turmeric</li>
                    <li>2 tablespoons oil</li>
                    <li>Salt to taste</li>
                </ul>



            </ul>


            <h3>Process:</h3>
            <ul>
                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:cyan">Outer Layer:</li></b>
                <li>Take a bowl, combine the all-purpose flour, 1 and 1/2 spoon of heated oil and adequate salt. Mix it well.</li>
                <li>Gradually add water and knead the mixture into a soft dough. Cover the dough with a damp cloth and keep it aside for about 30 minutes.</li>
                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:cyan">For Stuffing:</li></b>
                <li>Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pan, Add the finely chopped onions.</li>
                <li>Add red chili powder, garam masala, turmeric pwder, coriander powder and salt.</li>
                <li>Add green chillies at last saute it for a few minutes until onions turn into light gold colour and the mixture is dry.</li>
                <li>Divide the dough into small, equal-sized balls.</li>
                <b>
                <li style="text-decoration: underline;list-style-type:none;color:cyan">Samosa making:</li></b>
                <li>Roll out each ball into a thin oval or round shape</li>
                <li>Cut them into rectangles with high length and short width</li>
                <li>Take one recatangle, fold it in half to form a cone, and seal the edge with oil to make a triangular pocket.</li>
                <li>Fill the pocket with the prepared onion mixture. Seal the open edge by pressing it firmly with your fingers.</li>
                <li>Heat oil in a deep frying pan or kadai over medium heat.</li>
                <li>Carefully slide the prepared samosas into the hot oil. Fry them until they are golden brown and crispy.</li>
                <li>Remove the samosas with a slotted spoon and place them on a plate lined with paper towels to drain excess oil.</li>
                <li>Serve your homemade onion samosas </li>
            </ul>
            <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enjoy your homemade onion samosa :)</p>
